m_q.target_metric: The name of the building that was first designated as the tallest
filters: Years as tallest must contain a valid year range
Height ft (m) must contain valid height data
sub_questions: What is the earliest start year in Years as tallest column?
Which building corresponds to that earliest start year?
How should we handle buildings with the same start year?

scale_issues: Height ft (m) column contains both feet and meters in same string
Years as tallest contains ranges with en dash separator

format_notes: Years as tallest column uses en dash (–) as range separator
Height ft (m) column contains both imperial and metric units in parentheses
Some rows have missing data (e.g., Nicollet Mall row with '-' values)

constraints: Years as tallest must be parsed to extract start year
Rows with '-' in Years as tallest should be excluded
First building is determined by minimum start year
derived_filters: Exclude rows where Years as tallest = '-'
